### Describe the bug

Hi,
i'm expiriencing a strange bug, unfortunately i was not able to reproduce with the getting started version.

I'm migrating my production application from 2.16 to 3.2, i've migrated also to resteasy-reactive following the migration guides.

The application starts and it work normally in `dev` and `jvm` mode.
When compiled in `native` mode, i've found that 2 GET rest endpoint give the `NoSuchMethodException` when called.

This two endpoint is very very simple:

```
   @Inject
    @Location("LogoutProvider/logout.html")
    Template logout;

    @GET
    @Path("/logout.html")
    @Produces(value = MediaType.TEXT_HTML)
    public TemplateInstance logoutPage() {
        return logout.instance();
    }
```

The other one is:

```
@GET
    @Path("/timestamp")
    public Response timestamp() {
        try {

            Map<String, String> map = new HashMap<String, String>();
            map.put("epoch", "" + ZonedDateTime.now(ZoneId.systemDefault()).toEpochSecond());


            return Response.status(Response.Status.OK).entity(map).build();
        } catch (Exception e) {
            logger.error(e.getMessage(), e);
            return Response.serverError().entity(e.getMessage()).build();
        }
    }
```

The only thing i've found that is working, is annotating the class with the `@RegisterForReflection`.

Unfortunately i tried to reproduce with the "getting started" project, but i wasn't able to reproduce the bug.



